1. Open IntelliJ (if you are not in the welcome screen, click `File` > `Close Project` to close the existing project dialog first).
1. Set up the correct JDK version.
* Click `Configure` > `Structure for new Projects` (in older versions of Intellij:`Configure` > `Project Defaults` > `Project Structure`).
* If JDK 11 is listed in the drop down, select it. If it is not, click `New...` and select the directory where you installed JDK 11.
1. Locate the project directory and click `OK`.
1. Select `Create project from existing sources` and click `Next`.
1. Rename the project if you want. Click `Next`.
1. Ensure that your src folder is checked. Keep clicking `Next`.

* The DukeArgumentException class is an Exception that is thrown when there are either
* missing parameter or too many parameter provided by the user.
* DukeArgumentException class extends from IllegalArgumentException class.
* @param message Error message shown to the user.
* The DukeIndexException class is an Exception that is thrown when the index provided by
* the user is out of bound. In such cases, the index provided is either negative or greater
* than total number of Task stored.
* DukeIndexException class extends from IndexOutOfBoundsException class.
* @param message Error message shown to the user.
* The DukeNullException class is an Exception that is thrown when there is an invalid
* DukeNullException class extends from NullPointerException class.
* @param message Error message shown to the user.

* Deadline class extends from Task class.
* @param description Description of the Deadline Task.
* @param date Due date of the Deadline Task.

* Return a String representation of this Deadline.
* @return The Deadline's icon, followed by the Task's toString, followed by the due date.
* The Event class is a Task with specified description and date of occurrence.
* Event class extends from Task class.
* @param description Description of the Event Task.
* @param date Date of occurrence of the Event Task.
* Getter method for the date of occurrence.
* Return a String representation of this Event.
* @return The Event's icon, followed by the Task's toString, followed by the date of occurrence.
